The pair also released a calendar featuring Moongoyle Web hostess Violett Wolfe posing in lingerie that was 'popular with prison inmates' according to their Facebook page.

The Moongoyle site and YouTube channel have been taken down in the aftermath of this controversy.

'The administration and [Board of Education] are concerned about the judgment used to be engaged in such activities while serving as an educational leader.' Granby Superintendent Alan Addley said in a written statement.

'The investigation will begin immediately and is expected to conclude promptly.'

The Hartford Courant reports that Addley also added that there was no indication Foley had engaged in any illegal activity.

